 further apart by the zombies overtaking the city, Jae-yoon is forced to face his insecurities both as a new, clueless recruit protecting the country and as Young-joo&#39;s love interest, as the couple go through hoardes of the undead to find each other again in more ways than one.</p><h2> Who is in the cast of the new K-drama?</h2><p> Acclaimed Korean actor Park Jung-min, with recent appearances in <em>Harbin</em> and <em>Smugglers,</em> is set to star as Jae-yoon. He&#39;s a new South Korean military recruit, having enlisted years later than other soldiers. The series follows him as he is immediately put to battle following the zombie outbreak.</p><p> Playing Young-joo is BLACKPINK vocalist and <em><a href="https://www.nme.com/series/snowdrop">Snowdrop</a></em> star Jisoo. Known in college as the “goddess of the engineering department” for her looks, she is now a regular office worker who finds herself in the thick of the apocalypse.</p><p> Joining the pair in the supporting cast are Im Sung-jae, Hong Seo-hee, <em><a href="https://www.nme.com/series/crash-landing-on-you">Crash Landing On You</a> &#39;s</em> Tang Jun-sang, <em>The World of the Married&#39;s</em> Lee Hak-joo as well as <em>The Battleship Island&#39;s</em> Kim Jun-han.</p><p> <em>Newtopia</em> is notably written by <em>Parasite</em> screenwriter Han Jin-won and <em><a href="https://www.nme.com/series/a-shop-for-killers">A Shop For Killers</a> &#39;</em> Ji Ho-jin. Helming the series is Yoon Sung-hyun, who previously worked on 2010&#39;s <em>Bleak Night</em> and 2020&#39;s <em>Time To Hunt.</em></p><h2> Is there a trailer for <em>Newtopia?</em></h2><p> The first teaser for <em>Newtopia</em> dropped on January 15, opening with the moment Young-joo breaks up with Jae-yoon over the phone. It then launches into a montage of the sheer chaos that erupts when the zombie virus is spread across Seoul, focusing on the couple as they fight through the carnage to find each other. </p><p><iframe loading="lazy" title="Newtopia |第一个拖车|亚马逊Prime" width="696" height="392" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/86bXMN-kQK0?feature=oembed&enablejsapi=1" frameborder="0" allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share" referrerpolicy="strict-origin-when-cross-origin" allowfullscreen></iframe></p><p> On January 24, Coupang Play unveiled a new teaser for the series. It features Jae-yoon as he struggles to keep up as a military soldier, while Young-joo is seen missing Jae-yoon. When the zombie virus emerges, the couple begin to fight the zombies in their own ways in order to reunite. “I&#39;ll survive no matter what and come running to you,” Jae-yoon tells her. </p><p><iframe loading="lazy" title="纽约人 - 官方预告片|主要视频" width="696" height="392" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/HtaaO9D9ZcU?feature=oembed&enablejsapi=1" frameborder="0" allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share" referrerpolicy="strict-origin-when-cross-origin" allowfullscreen></iframe></p><p> Coupang Play and Amazon Prime unveiled a “character trailer” on February 7, introducing viewers to the show&#39;s quirky cast of characters. The clip introduces Jae-yoon and his laid-back approach to his military enlistment, as well as Young-joo with her curiosity and love for Jae-yoon despite their distance. </p><p><iframe loading="lazy" title="Newtopia |角色预告片|亚马逊Prime" width="696" height="392" src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/_8DU2vculYo?feature=oembed&enablejsapi=1" frameborder="0" allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share" referrerpolicy="strict-origin-when-cross-origin" allowfullscreen></iframe></p><h2> When will <em>Newtopia</em> premiere <em>?</em></h2><p> <i>Newtopia</i> will be hitting screens via Korean streaming platform Coupang Play on February 7 at 8pm KST. The series will also be made available to stream via Prime Video in select regions.</